    <item>
      <title>Colouring in the connectome with neurotransmitters</title>
      <link>https://as-bates.netlify.app/portfolio/neurotransmitters/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 09 May 2024 10:00:00 -0400</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://as-bates.netlify.app/portfolio/neurotransmitters/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;p&gt;The fly now has a full connectome, a directed and weighted graph of its neurons. But what are its connection signs, excitatory or inhibitory? Our work in &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cell.2024.03.016&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cell&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; moves towards that answer by predicting neurotransmitters directly from electron microscopy.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
